    "timestamp": "2026-02-04T00:50:29+00:00",
    "caption": "YРђЎall really showed up ­ЪЎї\n\nWe wanted to share a quick update from Friday Рђћ and to say thank you.\n\nGoing into the day, we were honestly a little nervous. Fridays are usually slow, and we worried we might not raise enough to make the donation feel meaningful.\n\nInstead, we had 35% more check-ins than a typical Friday, and raised $3,260 to donate to immigrant support organizations.\n\nWeРђЎre grateful for our members and the broader Bay Area climbing community Рђћ for coming out, for climbing with intention, and for supporting immigrants Рђћ many of yРђЎalls took pay-what-you-can to a higher level and gave extra on top of a day pass or a shirt to help support the cause!\n\nFriday reminded us why community spaces matter, and why we believe so strongly in building and protecting them together. This work will never end, so letРђЎs keep showing up for one another!\n\nWith love,\nBenchmark Climbing",
