  {
    "shortcode": "DUHQyjDEj7T",
    "url": "https://www.instagram.com/p/DUHQyjDEj7T/",
    "timestamp": "2026-01-29T23:43:58+00:00",
    "caption": "We at Benchmark Climbing are immigrants or children of immigrants, and many of our staff and community share similar stories. Recent events involving immigration enforcement Рђћ including tragedies that have deeply harmed families and communities Рђћ have shaken us. We are grieving, and we stand with those impacted.\n\nAs a community space built around healing and support, we asked ourselves how to truly live BenchmarkРђЎs value of positive progression. We considered closing for the general strike, but ultimately felt it was important to bear the financial impact ourselves rather than pass that cost onto staff or members.\n\nClimbing is more than a sport Рђћ for many people itРђЎs essential to physical and mental health. Benchmark is a safe, inclusive space for people of all backgrounds, and we want it to remain available to anyone who needs it.\n\nThis Friday, January 30, our gyms will remain open.\n\nAll proceeds Рђћ from day passes, coaching, youth programs, retail, food, and beverages Рђћ will be donated to the Immigration Institute of the Bay Area and Unidos MN. We chose these organizations because they provide both direct legal support to immigrants locally and community-based support at the grassroots level for immigrant families in Minnesota.\n\nWe will also host an on-site station to help people donate, contact representatives, and support immigrant communities and due process.\n\nWe are offering pay-what-you-can day passes for anyone who supports or participates in protests, or who has donated to immigration-focused mutual aid groups or nonprofits.\n\nCommunity spaces exist so we can decide together what kind of world we want to live in. Thank you for helping make Benchmark a home for all.\n\nWith love,\nBenchmark Climbing\n\n@unidosmn \n@iiba1918",
